From cc8a4cf97bf05480b8c94c4be3b4d7ff625f16dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Aug 2025 16:21:07 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:hostapd: ATF: Add stats support for ATF

New vendor NL attributes and CLI commands to manage ATF
(Airtime Fairness) statistics reporting.
The following cli commands are added:

1. Enable/Disable ATF Stats Collection
   - New NL attribute to enable or disable ATF stats reporting
   - CLI command: `enable_atf_stats`
   - CLI command: `g_enable_atf_stats` to query current enable status

2. Configure ATF Stats Timeout
   - New NL attribute to set the ATF stats timeout period
   - CLI command: `atf_stats_timeout` to set the timeout.
		  atf_stats_timeout range is 10 - 50 seconds.
   - CLI command: `g_atf_stats_timeout` to get the current timeout value

cli commands:
MLO:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  enable_atf_stats  1/0
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  g_enable_atf_stats
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload atf_stats_timeout <time>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  g_atf_stats_timeout 

Legacy:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  enable_atf_stats  1/0
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  g_enable_atf_stats
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload atf_stats_timeout <time>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  g_atf_stats_timeout

The stats timeout defines the interval at which ATF statistics are printed.

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
